6</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Keri</gtr:firstName><gtr:otherNames>Lee</gtr:otherNames><gtr:surname>Facer</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole><gtr:personRole url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/A229AF1C-73AE-48AA-84CA-F52588594762"><gtr:id>A229AF1C-73AE-48AA-84CA-F52588594762</gtr:id><gtr:firstName>Carey</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Jewitt</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>CO_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/projects?ref=ES%2FH001786%2F1"><gtr:id>AFD1D643-1767-4DCE-9263-6C78C265BA84</gtr:id><gtr:title>Educational Futures: the theory, methods and ethics of futures-oriented research in education</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Research Grant</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/H001786/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>This seminar series brought together education researchers, practitioners and policy makers with futures-oriented researchers from a range of disciplines including computer science, bioethics, computing, scenario planning and environmental movements. The aim was to explore how education research might develop more reflective and critical ways of thinking about, researching and acting on ideas of the future.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The series involved four seminars, a conference for education leaders and a public debate at the RSA. The seminars examined:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>&amp;nbsp;the rationale for futures-oriented education research&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>&amp;nbsp;theoretical frameworks for such research&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>&amp;nbsp;methods and techniques for futures-oriented research&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>&amp;nbsp;ethical issues.&lt;/li>

&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>The seminar series made visible the wide variety of theoretical and methodological approaches to ?researching? the future in education and other disciplines and led to a freely available publication called ?Building Agency in the Face of Uncertainty? (http://edfuturesresearch.org/downloads). This explores this diversity of possible futures-orientations and addresses common questions about the purpose, ethics and value of futures-oriented reflection in education&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The series has led to: new international collaborations, two books, a Special Issue, and the use of the ?building agency? publication in teacher education, educational policy development in Finland and Singapore, and in Masters education programmes.&lt;br />&lt;br />&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2011-07-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2009-10-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>15044</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Cabot Annual Lecture</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>National</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>0F46DBCE-7A72-4361-88C6-D8A6DA1168EB</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Major Annual Lecture for the Cabot Institute - Environmental Change Institute. Focused on the long term role of universities in society.</gtr:impact><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Public/other audiences</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:url>http://www.bristol.ac.uk/cabot/events/2016/annual-lecture-2016.html</gtr:url><gtr:year>2016</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput></gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:description>We have discovered that dispositions toward the future are framed by the assumptions people operate with relating to two axes: their perception of their own agency (capacity to effect change in the future) and their perception of their knowledge of the future (whether the future is seen as knowable or uncertain). Encouraging individuals and groups to reflect on these assumptions provides a foundation for more agile 'uses' of the future in planning and decision making.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The resources designed to support reflection on the relationship between education and the future are widely available and already being used by educators in the UK and around the world. 

These resources have recently (2016) been included in a set of guidance for teachers in Italy and in Canada. They were also used in training for school leaders, union leaders, academics, college leaders in events from 2012 - the present.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>1DD40372-C19D-4F28-9408-7904DED27DD8</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Education,Government, Democracy and Justice</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>https://www.academia.edu/21661718/A_thinking_tool_for_educators_and_education_leaders</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/A0EFEF6A-2280-431D-862B-31C4B73F679E"><gtr:id>A0EFEF6A-2280-431D-862B-31C4B73F679E</gtr:id><gtr:title>Learning Futures: Education, Technology and Social Change</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/d28e1642ee1c67f28bbc0c328b9835ec"><gtr:id>d28e1642ee1c67f28bbc0c328b9835ec</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Facer Keri</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2011-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>9780415581424</gtr:isbn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/10870D87-F703-4A77-B2B0-400656D0374F"><gtr:id>10870D87-F703-4A77-B2B0-400656D0374F</gtr:id><gtr:title>Creativity and Education Futures: Learning in a Digital Age</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/6a9c3e3c024bd0d52707a797365339af"><gtr:id>6a9c3e3c024bd0d52707a797365339af</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Craft Anna</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:isbn>9781858564623</gtr:isbn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/8C6B1498-BF2D-4C51-B7AF-D4F38FE1EA87"><gtr:id>8C6B1498-BF2D-4C51-B7AF-D4F38FE1EA87</gtr:id><gtr:title>Usi